{% if bootstrap is defined and bootstrap %}## Bootstrap

`bootstrap.md` declares the canonical install/run/test/UAT commands for this
project. Prefer these over ad-hoc construction. Order of preference:
docker compose > Makefile target > package.json script > raw command.

{{ bootstrap }}

{% endif %}{% if env_requirements is defined and env_requirements %}## Environment

`env_requirements.md` lists every variable the project reads, classified as
**auto** (safe default exists), **mock** (mock service shipped), or **human**
(real credential required). Human-required values live in
`.agentic-dev/secrets.env` and are loaded into your process environment
before you are dispatched.

{{ env_requirements }}

{% endif %}**Use canonical commands first.** When you start servers or run
the application, prefer the command from `bootstrap.md` (typically
`docker compose -f docker-compose.e2e.yml up -d` for web-stack projects
with an e2e compose file). For long-running builds, redirect output to a
file and watch it for a readiness regex — never stream raw build logs into
your context.
